---
title: Apple Sage Turkey Burgers with Garlic Mayo and Cranberry Walnut Salad
description: Turkey burgers all too often turn out dry, but we’ve discovered the sweet secret to keeping them moist: apples. The grated fruit is blended into the meat, which along with breadcrumbs, herbs, and garlic does an astonishing job of giving you everything you want in a patty. To continue the fruit-forward fall theme, we’ve also added a salad to the side that incorporates cranberries, walnuts, and a lemon dressing.*Please note that this recipe may be packaged with samples that contain peanuts, tree nuts and milk.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/apple-sage-turkey-burgers-9fa05f8d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/apple-sage-turkey-burgers-2196a297.pdf
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/apple-sage-turkey-burgers-59baf041a2882a1c3e1d5902
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 440 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Pick and finely chop enough @sage{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems to give you 2 TBSP. Halve and core @Fuji apple{1}. Slice one half into ½-inch-thick slices; grate other half into a #large bowl{}. Halve @lemon{1}.

Stir together @mayonnaise{4%tbsp} and a pinch of garlic in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @ground turkey{20%oz}, chopped sage, and remaining garlic to bowl with grated apple. Season with salt and pepper (we used 1 1/2 tsp kosher salt). Thoroughly combine and form into four 1-inch-thick patties.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use an #ovenproof pan{} if you have one). Add burgers to pan and cook until browned on bottom, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip burgers, then place pan in oven. (TIP: Transfer burgers to a #baking sheet{} if your pan is not ovenproof.) Cook until no longer pink in center, about ~{10%minutes}.

Split @brioche buns{4} in half and place on a baking sheet. Toast in oven until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Toss @mixed greens{1%oz}, @dried cranberries{2%oz}, @walnuts{1%oz}, a squeeze of lemon, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in another large bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread buns with garlic mayo and fill with burgers. Top with apple slices and a few leaves of lettuce from salad. Serve with salad on the side.